sp.p:
So 'twould appear that beauty is invested in bank-stock;
grace consolidated with the landed interests; while reputation
fluctuates with the three and a half per cents.

Can May-fair legislation so repeal the laws of nature;
by Jove! the west end at last, will cut the sun because it
rises in the east, and live by wax light.

I trust you don't swear, Charles — I mean in English;
and excuse the anxiety of a mother — you continue to
use the almond paste I wrote to you about?

Ha! ha! what a strange notion;
(aside)
can it be so striking as to betray me?
